The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Wipro profit confirms green shoots theory
                                                                                                               Wipro profit confirms green shoots theory
          OUR BUREAU                                            
	Oct. 27: Wipro Ltd today reported a 19 per cent growth in consolidated net profit at Rs 1,162 crore for the July-September quarter, helped by a better economic environment and stability in prices.         
	The countrys third largest software exporter had a net profit of Rs 978.2 crore in the corresponding quarter a year ago.        
	Revenue grew 6 per cent to Rs 6,917 crore, the company said.        
	In rupee terms, revenue from IT services was Rs 4,996 crore, a year-on-year growth of 5 per cent and a sequential growth of 3.5 per cent. In dollar terms it declined 4 per cent year-on-year to $1,065.2 million.        
	Wipro chairman Azim Premji said, The macro environment is stabilising and the improving business landscape that we had talked about last quarter is playing out in reality. Our IT services business was at the top end of our guidance in constant currency and exceeded guidance by 1.2 per cent on a reported basis.        
	Buoyed by the good show, Wipro emerged as the biggest gainer among the frontline stocks, gaining 2.18 per cent on the Bombay Stock Exchange on a day when the sensex tumbled nearly 400 points. The scrip rose Rs 12.90 over the previous close of Rs 604.15.         
	The companys IT services business saw 37 new clients during the quarter.         
	IT products business recorded an 18 per cent year-on-year growth in revenues.         
	McLeod net         
	McLeod Russel has reported a net profit of Rs 192.19 crore during the quarter ended September 30 against Rs 121.73 crore a year ago.         
	Net sales rose to Rs 343.77 crore during the quarter from Rs 279.20 crore in the year-ago period.        
	During the first six months, McLeods net profit rose 73 per cent to Rs 223.37 crore from Rs 128.81 crore in the same period last year.                                                                                                                                        
